Q6. What is the best way to make a Unicode text file in a particular encoding format?
Ans. Pass the required encoding name to open in 3 to generate a Unicode text file in that format. When X strings are written to a file, they are encoded according to the selected encoding.

Q7. What qualifies ASCII text as a form of Unicode text?
Ans. Because its 7-bit value range is a subset of most Unicode encodings, ASCII text is considered a kind of Unicode text. As a result, Unicode is backwards compatible with the vast majority of ASCII text data on the planet.

